{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"898fc1c7-f89a-437f-a9f4-90df12047118","content":"Two things change with xUnit.net v3 + MTP:\n\n1. **`--filter` (VSTest syntax) is no longer used.** MTP uses `--treenode-filter` instead.\n2. **The syntax is path/glob-based**, with trait filters in square brackets.\n\nYour translated CI command:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n**Breakdown:**\n\n| Old (VSTest) | New (MTP treenode-filter) |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `/**/*IntegrationTests*` (glob match on test tree) |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` (trait property filter) |\n| `&` (AND) | Combined inline — the `[...]` applies to the matched nodes |\n\nThe `--` separates `dotnet test` args from arguments passed directly to the MTP runner. Your `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` attribute and test structure are fine as-is — no code changes needed, only the CLI invocation.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f51302de-11e6-42af-851f-8ae9cb988414","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is migrating from xUnit v2 to xUnit v3 with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). The key changes for filtering:\n\n1. With MTP, `dotnet test` uses a different filter syntax. The `--filter` flag from VSTest is replaced by `--filter` in MTP but with different semantics.\n\n2. In xUnit v3 with MTP:\n   - `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` → The FQN filter still works but the syntax changes\n   - `Category=Smoke` → Traits are accessed differently\n\nWith MTP (Microsoft.Testing.Platform), the filter syntax changes:\n\n\n- Operators like `~` (contains) and `&` (and) are replaced with word-based equivalents like `contains` and `and`\n- Property references use different notation, often with `/` prefixes or specific property names instead of VSTest's approach\n- Trait filtering requires a different syntax than the simple `Category=Smoke` format\n\nWith MTP enabled, I have two main filtering strategies: using `--treenode-filter` for path-based filtering like `/**/*IntegrationTests*`, or using `--filter` with MTP's filter expressions. The challenge is that MTP uses MSTest filter syntax, which means operators and property references work differently than VSTest—I need to figure out exactly how xUnit v3 maps traits like `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` under MTP and what the correct filter syntax becomes. The VSTest `--filter` syntax with traits doesn't translate directly to MTP, so I need to use `--treenode-filter` with glob patterns for name-based filtering instead, or rely on MTP's own filter syntax which handles metadata like traits differently than VSTest does. to the test runner, so the `--` separator passes the tree-node filter directly to MTP, which then matches test nodes by name pattern and filters them by the Category trait.","outputTokens":1496},"id":"1ea75dea-e684-43a4-9fb2-665c3ecfe8cb","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:59:36.333Z","parentId":"e84a62af-374d-4a30-9487-18d4b07ecf0a"}
